    "body": "<b>edit) Sorry. I thought it was a question about ethclient. Please ignore it.</b>\r\n\r\nI don't know the history, but the two variable about PendingBlockNumber are different.\r\nSo, If you want data about pending block, use like below\r\n```go\r\n// Get balance from pending block\r\n\r\n// bad\r\nclient.BalanceAt(context.Background(), \"\", rpc.PendingBlockNumber)\r\n\r\n// correct\r\nclient.BalanceAt(context.Background(), \"\", big.NewInt(-1))\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn rpc modules,\r\n```go\r\nconst (\r\n\tSafeBlockNumber      = BlockNumber(-4)\r\n\tFinalizedBlockNumber = BlockNumber(-3)\r\n\tPendingBlockNumber   = BlockNumber(-2)\r\n\tLatestBlockNumber    = BlockNumber(-1)\r\n\tEarliestBlockNumber  = BlockNumber(0)\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd ethclient\r\n```go\r\nfunc toBlockNumArg(number *big.Int) string {\r\n\tif number == nil {\r\n\t\treturn \"latest\"\r\n\t}\r\n\tpending := big.NewInt(-1)\r\n\tif number.Cmp(pending) == 0 {\r\n\t\treturn \"pending\"\r\n\t}\r\n\tfinalized := big.NewInt(int64(rpc.FinalizedBlockNumber))\r\n\tif number.Cmp(finalized) == 0 {\r\n\t\treturn \"finalized\"\r\n\t}\r\n\tsafe := big.NewInt(int64(rpc.SafeBlockNumber))\r\n\tif number.Cmp(safe) == 0 {\r\n\t\treturn \"safe\"\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn hexutil.EncodeBig(number)\r\n}\r\n```",
